# Cline Rules
# This file is read by the Cline VS Code extension for AI context
# Keep in sync with .github/copilot-instructions.md for consistency

You are an expert software engineer. Follow these project guidelines:

## Code Style

- Write clean, readable code with meaningful variable and function names
- Follow language-idiomatic conventions and community standards
- Prefer composition over inheritance; favor small, focused functions
- Use consistent naming: camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes/types
- Keep functions under 30 lines; extract helpers for complex logic
- Use early returns to reduce nesting

## Architecture

- Follow separation of concerns (controllers, services, repositories)
- Use dependency injection for testability
- Keep business logic out of route handlers and UI components

## Testing

- All new code must include unit tests
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
- Test behavior, not implementation
- Cover happy path, edge cases, and error cases

## Security

- Validate all user input at system boundaries
- Use parameterized queries for database operations
- Never log sensitive data
- Never hardcode secrets; use environment variables

## Error Handling

- Handle errors explicitly; no silent catches
- Include context in error messages
- Use typed errors where available

## Git

- Conventional commits: type(scope): description
- One logical change per PR
